  "prompt": "Why is cellphone called as cellphone?",
  "response": "The term \"cellphone\" is derived from the way these devices operate within a network. Cellphones connect to a cellular network, which is divided into smaller geographical areas called \"cells.\" Each cell is equipped with a base station that facilitates communication within its area. As a user moves from one cell to another, the call is seamlessly handed off from one base station to the next, ensuring continuous connectivity. Thus, the name \"cellphone\" reflects the cellular architecture of the network that enables mobile communication.",
